@crazyreaper: When asking for help on a bulletin board for something as important as a dissertation, be sure to cite it properly, lest your committee bust you for plagiarism. According to APA 6.0 the proper way to do this is:

Dean, C. (2012, October 24). Re: Thread title (Online forum comment). Retrieved from [http://url](http://web.archive.org/web/20130214111201/http:/url/ "http://url") of the thread

In this case, replace my name and date with the time and person who answered your question.
